[[File:Salzburg Hbf being renovated.jpg|thumb|right|Salzurg Hauptbahnhof being renovated in July 2010.]]
{{Hbf intro|Salzburg}} is the [[Hauptbahnhof]] at [[Salzburg]], capital of the [[States of Austria|federal state]] of [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]] in [[Austria]]. It is the most important station in the agglomeration of Salzburg, and a major transportation hub in western Austria.

==Overview==
For a long time, the station has also been a border station at the Austrian border with [[Germany]]. It serves both the [[Austrian Federal Railways]] (<U+00D6>BB) and the [[Deutsche Bahn AG]]. It also forms a [[Junction (rail)|junction]] between several <U+00D6>BB local and long-distance transport routes.

At Salzburg Hbf, the [[Western Railway (Austria)|Wester Railway]] from [[Vienna]] and [[Linz]] links with the [[Munich<U+2013>Salzburg railway]], on which, along with international trains, so-called <U+00D6>BB corridor services make express connections with the [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]] and the [[Vorarlberg]], via the ''German Corner'' at [[Rosenheim]]. Another main line, the Salzburg-Tyrol railway, heads from Salzburg Hbf in a southerly direction via [[Bischofshofen]] and [[Zell am See]] to [[W<U+00F6>rgl Hauptbahnhof]]. In [[Schwarzach im Pongau|Schwarzach]]-[[St. Veit]], yet another main line, the [[Tauern Railway]], branches off from this line. 

The station is also important as a departure point for regional services on the Salzburger Lokalbahn, and as a key hub of the [[Salzburg S-Bahn]] and for many regional buses serving Greater Salzburg. Also located at the station is one of the key hubs in the StadtBus Salzburg city bus network.

Until 1957, a local railway station in the Salzburg Hbf forecourt was the departure point for the [[narrow gauge]] [[SKGLB-Museum|Salzkammergut-Lokalbahn]], commonly known as the ''Ischlerbahn'', to [[Mondsee]] and [[Bad Ischl]].

== Present-day services ==
Today the station is a stop for [[Intercity-Express|ICE]] and [[InterCity|IC]] long-distance trains, as well as local trains operated by [[Deutsche Bahn]] (DB AG) and the [[Austrian Federal Railways]] (<U+00D6>BB). The station is also a loading point for [[Motorail]] trains.<ref>[http://www.oebb.at/pv/de/Rund_ums_Reisen/Autoreisezug/ARZ_Anfahrtsplaene/Download_PDF/Salzburg.pdf Description of <U+00D6>BB Autoreisezug Autoverladestelle Salzburg Hauptbahnhof (Pdf-file)] {{de-icon}}</ref>

